!! Jesus Heals a Man with an Unclean Demon (v31-v37)
We see now that Jesus leaves and goes down to Capernaum in Galilee. As he was teaching on Sabbath, he goes and rebukes an unclean spirit. Before so the unclean spirit says:

<<<
Ha! What have you to do with us, Jesus of Nazareth? Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are—the Holy One of God.
<<<
''Luke 4:34''

''Even the demons knew who He was! What makes the believer different from the unbeliever? That we know and obey Jesus' commands by practicing them.''

<<<
But someone will say, “You have faith and I have works.” Show me your faith apart from your works, and I will show you my faith by my works. You believe that God is one; you do well. Even the demons believe—and shudder! 
<<<
''James 2:18-19''

Mark 1 is the parallel passage for this section and gives more of an account. We see that Jesus' fame starting to spread as He performed these miracles.

!! Jesus Heals Many (v38-41)
Once more we see Jesus heal the sick and had authority over demons. He continued to do so until even the "sun was setting." His compassion was great. It wasn't until it was day that he departed (v42). He spent all night healing and helping the sick!

!! Jesus Preaches in Synagogues (v42-44)
''Even after leaving while healing the entire night, we folks pursuing him to be healed.'' But Jesus was not deterred by the crowds and decides to leave as Jesus understood His mission, "I must preach the good news of the Kingdom of God to the other towns as well; for I was sent for this purpose." Once more affirming what He quoted in Isaiah 61:1-2a:

<<<
The Spirit of the Lord God is upon me,
    because the Lord has anointed me
to bring good news to the poor;
    he has sent me to bind up the brokenhearted,
to proclaim liberty to the captives,
    and the opening of the prison to those who are bound;
to proclaim the year of the Lord's favor,
<<<

Thus he goes to preach in Judea.